Opinion bt
Mb. Justice Mitchell,
For reasons given in the opinion filed herewith in W. W. & I. H. Brownfield’s Appeal, January term, No. 279, ante, p. 151, these appeals are dismissed at the costs of the appellees.
opinions.author: Mb. Justice Mitchell,

Estate of Isaac Brownfield. Appeals of Malinda Brownfield.
Argued May 8, 1899.
Appeals, Nos. 23 and 274, Jan. T., 1898, by Malinda Brownfield, from decree of O. C. Fayette Co., Sept. T., 1895, No. 43, dismissing exceptions to auditor’s report.
Before Stebbett, C. J., Gbeen, McCollum, Mitch: ell, Dean and Fell, JJ.
Appeal dismissed.
October 6, 1899:
